  "subject": "refactor(debug): harden DEBUG_SYSTEM вЂ” separate root, console capture,",
  "body": "Environment tab, typed details, pre-React pill, replay, HMR guard\n\nAll 11 items from the DEBUG_SYSTEM hardening task landed in one\ncoherent refactor. Previously synctone's debug surface was one\nRN-based `PWADebugBanner` component rendered inside the main React\ntree with 2 tabs; it shared the app's ErrorBoundary (so an app\ncrash took it down), mixed Tailwind + inline styles, silently\nswallowed console warnings, had no HMR guard (hot-reload duplicated\nglobal error listeners), no pre-mount error capture, no subscriber\nreplay, no entry IDs, and string-only `detail` payloads.\n\n## Part A вЂ” Separate React root\n\n- `utils/debugRootMount.ts`: new. Side-effect-import-able web-only\n  module that `createRoot`'s into `<div id=\"debug-root\">` in the\n  HTML template and renders `DebugPill`. Idempotent via the\n  `window.__debugMounted` flag.\n- `app/+html.tsx`: adds `<div id=\"debug-root\"></div>` before\n  `{children}`, and a substantial pre-React inline `<script>` (Part E\n  below).\n- `app/_layout.tsx`: removes `<PWADebugBanner />` from the Slot\n  tree; adds `import '@/utils/debugRootMount'` at the top as a\n  side-effect import. DebugPill no longer lives in the main tree вЂ”\n  Error Boundary trips and render crashes in synctone code can't\n  unmount it.\n- `components/PWADebugBanner.tsx`: deleted. Replaced by\n  `components/debug/DebugPill.tsx` (pure DOM, inline styles вЂ” see\n  Part D below).\n\n## Part B вЂ” Console interception\n\n`utils/debugLog.ts` at module load (dev only, HMR-guarded, web only):\ncaptures `console.error` + `console.warn`, pushes a structured\nentry (`{ message, args }`) into the debug log, then delegates\nthrough to the original method so DevTools + native Expo logs are\nunaffected. Original methods are snapshotted BEFORE any other\nmodule can intercept them, so this module's own error paths can\ncall `originalConsole.error(...)` without re-triggering the\nintercept (avoids loops).\n\n## Part C вЂ” Environment tab\n\nThird tab in DebugPill. Snapshot (not stream) of: URL (query\nredacted), userAgent, screen + viewport dimensions, `online`,\nprotocol, `display-mode: standalone` + `navigator.standalone`,\nSW/IndexedDB support, `navigator.language`, ISO timestamp. Computed\nlazily when the tab is opened so the snapshot reflects current\nstate, not mount-time state.\n\n## Part D вЂ” Pure DOM + inline styles\n\nDebugPill rewritten as a plain React component using DOM elements\n(`<div>`, `<button>`, `<span>`) and hardcoded `CSSProperties` inline\nstyles. No `useTheme`, no Tailwind, no react-native-web. Pill\nrenders correctly even when:\n - Uniwind CSS fails to load (404)\n - theme context isn't initialized\n - react-native-web init throws\nHardcoded palette in the file (synthwave-themed).\n\n## Part E вЂ” Pre-React inline pill\n\n`app/+html.tsx` gets ~100 lines of inline `<script>` that runs\nsynchronously from HTML parse. It:\n 1. Installs `window.onerror` and `window.onunhandledrejection`\n    listeners BEFORE the Expo bundle loads.\n 2. Captures each error into `window.__debugPreMountQueue` (array).\n 3. Renders a minimal DOM pill (no React) at top-right with the\n    queued error count. Clicking it shows the errors in an alert().\n 4. At 20s, if `window.__debugMounted` is still false, escalates\n    with a \"React debug pill failed to mount\" entry вЂ” the Expo\n    bundle has probably failed to load.\n 5. Polls for React mount and removes the fallback DOM pill once\n    the React pill takes over.\n\nDebugPill on mount drains the queue via `debugLog('global',\n'pre-mount-error', ...)` so those errors appear in the Log tab\nalongside runtime-captured entries. Also replaces\n`window.__debugPushError` with a direct `debugLog()` call.\n\nShips in production (not just dev) because bundle-load failure is\nexactly when a production user needs to see SOMETHING on screen.\n~1.5 KB of inline script, zero dependencies.\n\n## Part F вЂ” Clipboard fallback chain\n\n`copyToClipboardWithFallback(text)` tries three approaches in order:\n 1. `ClipboardItem` + `navigator.clipboard.write()` (rich, best UX)\n 2. `navigator.clipboard.writeText()` (widely supported but\n    rejected on some mobile Safari)\n 3. Hidden `<textarea>` + `document.execCommand('copy')` (deprecated\n    but universally available вЂ” critical for mobile Safari)\nCopy button shows \"Copied!\" / \"Copy failed\" for 1.5s.\n\n## Part G вЂ” Module-level debugGenerateReport\n\n`debugGenerateReport(): string` now lives in `utils/debugLog.ts`\nand can be called from anywhere (tests, future telemetry hooks,\nCLI dumps). Bundles environment snapshot + every log entry with\nquery-redacted URLs into a plain-text report. `collectEnvironment()`\nalso exported for direct consumption.\n\n## Part H вЂ” HMR guard\n\n`utils/debugLog.ts` global listeners + console interception are\nattached behind `window.__debugLogListenersAttached`. Hot-reload\nre-executing the module no longer stacks N copies of every error\nin the log. Flag declared on `Window` in `types/rn-web-style.d.ts`\n(not `window as any` вЂ” synctone's convention since the type-safety\npass in d314346).\n\n## Part I вЂ” Typed `details: Record<string, unknown>`\n\n`DebugEntry.detail?: string` в†’ `DebugEntry.details?: Record<string,\nunknown>`. Backwards-compatible signature: `debugLog(...)` accepts\neither `string | Record<string, unknown>` and normalizes string\ninputs into `{ message: str }` before storing. Existing 95 call\nsites across the repo keep working without churn; new call sites\ncan pass structured payloads like `{ url, status, duration }` for\ngranular reporting. The Log-tab renderer unwraps single-key\n`{ message: ... }` shapes back to a bare string display so old\nentries look the same as before.\n\n## Part J вЂ” Numeric id per entry\n\n`let _nextId = 1`; each push assigns `entry.id = _nextId++`. Used\nas the React `key` in the Log tab's map вЂ” eliminates the previous\narray-index key warning and gives stable identity across re-renders.\n\n## Part K вЂ” Subscriber replay + error isolation\n\n`subscribeDebugLog(fn)`:\n - Synchronously replays every current entry to the new subscriber\n   so late-mounting consumers (including DebugPill in its separate\n   root that mounts AFTER module load) never miss entries.\n - Notify loop wraps each subscriber in try/catch so one throwing\n   listener can't break others on the same push.\nErrors inside subscribers surface via `originalConsole.error`\n(not the intercepted `console.error`) to avoid recursive capture\nloops.\n\n## Verification\n\n`tsc --noEmit` в†’ 0 errors.\nPre-React inline script: `new Function(body)` parse passes.\nTouched 9 files total; net +~800 lines of new code (substantial\ndue to inline pill, diagnostic tab, and palette) against deletion\nof the 383-line PWADebugBanner.\n\nLive-browser verification of all 11 items (crash-survives-via-\nseparate-root, console interception capture, pre-mount error drain,\nclipboard fallback chain on mobile Safari, HMR single-attach) is\ntracked in docs/TODO.md В§ High Priority as part of the existing\nlive-browser test pass.\n\n## Type augmentations\n\nAdded to `types/rn-web-style.d.ts`:\n - `Window.__debugLogListenersAttached` вЂ” HMR guard for console\n   interception + error listeners.\n - `Window.__debugMounted` вЂ” set true by DebugPill on mount; used\n   by the inline pill's 20s timeout + poll-to-hide logic.\n - `Window.__debugPushError` вЂ” bridge API the inline pill exposes\n   pre-mount; replaced by the React pill once it mounts.\n - `Window.__debugPreMountQueue` вЂ” array of errors captured by\n   the inline pill before React could run.\nAll typed, no `window as any`.\n\n## Docs\n\nCLAUDE.md updates:\n - Project Structure: adds `components/debug/DebugPill.tsx` and\n   `utils/debugRootMount.ts`; updates debugLog.ts description.\n - В§ Pattern Adoption Status: DEBUG_SYSTEM row rewritten to list\n   every hardening item; Z_INDEX_SCALE row updated to reflect\n   DebugPill's deliberate-outside-the-scale z-index choice.\n - В§ Z-Index Scale: `Z.debug` row updated вЂ” reserved for main-tree\n   debug UI; actual DebugPill uses hardcoded `2147483647` in its\n   separate root.\n\nTags: debug, diagnostics, types, refactor, fleet-alignment\nComplexity: 4\nUrgency: 2\nImpact: internal\nRisk: low\nDebt: paid\nEpic: fleet-alignment\nSemver: minor",
